	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Must agree with Corlathist, we are enough of a pet class that we should share in pet augments.  Multiple pets/upgrades, pet specific spells, and pet specific aa's.  If we are not a pet class, then why all the pet related spells and aa's?  <br />
<br />
Saying something does not make it true, reality is often quite different.  Whether SoE says we are a pet class or not, I can tell you that since I got my first doggy I've had him by my side constantly.  He may not have 4500 hp or proc/bs/cast, etc., but he is a part of the tactics and playing style that most shaman use.<br />
<br />
And yes, if a druid or SK decides to use their pet as an integral part of their playing strategy, I'd consider them a pet class.  They don't for obvious reasons, but most shaman do.<br />
<br />
If SoE has given us pet affinity and is still proposing upgraded pets in Omens, then we should be able to use the pet augments and spells in LDoN, IMHO.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
