	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Maybe this is narrow minded of me.<br />
<br />
But considering there are - what - THREE pet focus items in the game, I'll concentrate on one, the gloves from VT.  Last time we went, they dropped.  The guild mage other than my man had em.  There was one necro there who could've bid, but he didn't - because he knew he didn't feel as tied to his pet as my dear mage did.<br />
<br />
What if the bored as hell shamans could've bid on that thing?  Again, maybe this is just the wrong way to think about it, but I would've been extremely pissed off if some shaman had outbid him on this for a toy to push dogdog from 30dps to 33dps instead of pushing HIS pet from 100dps to 110 (or whatever it is).  Hell, shamans aren't even ALLOWED pets on raids (with my old guild)... but you know some bonehead would bid.<br />
<br />
Do you REALLY think it wouldn't be stupid for an enchanter to outbid you on a BA focus item?  Maybe that's because enchanter dots are as much of a joke as dogdog is?<br />
<br />
The only one I can agree to is the LDoN point-buy augment, because getting that won't screw any REAL pet class out of something that'll make a difference for em.  Poochie is a lot of fun, but it's hardly a battle that's going to help the shaman class out.<br />
<br />
(why do I get the sinking feeling that they'll implement this and it'll be our "fix"?)</p>
	
	
	
	
	
