</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>All I have to say on this is:<br />
<br />
Despite not being true healers, rangers and beastlords can still use and benefit from items with healing focus effects. <br />
<br />
Classes that are not dps caster classes and those that are not even true spell casters can still benefit from improved damage focuses (even effects procs)<br />
<br />
Classes that are not true melee can still use (or miss use dpending on how you see it) effects that boost their attack etc.<br />
<br />
Hell, even classes without a use for endurance can rack up massive ammounts of it.<br />
<br />
So why can't a psuedo pet class use a pet focus. The precedent has been set that other classes can use things not necessarily meant for them - just to a lower degree of usefulness.<br />
<br />
Thats my opinion of it in any event.</p>
	
	
	
